review_blob: Bottle and draught. As always with Dugges, pleasant aroma and lots of hops. Lots of coffee and chocolate in the aroma. Still some hint of chinook or something in the background. This one and some really good vanilla ice cream!
What to say? I like it. I love the fruity aroma. Its like sticking your head into a bag of Chinook hops.
I cant figure out the aroma. Citrus and something else such as  lavender. Pale, yellow with a nice head. A well balanced body and bitterness. Really nice with clams!

This beer is excellent a warm afternoon after work by the sea. The aroma is so special thanks to the beer being "dry hopped" with Simcoe hop. The body is a bit thin but thats probably due to the low alcohol percentage and I havent found any other 2.8 % beer thats better.
Wow! This new hop is making it even better than last times Ive tried it. Wow. Thats all I can say.
Very different to what I had expected. A pleasant fruity smell. Yet I find bitter flavors s.a. Seville orange. I will have it again.
